Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the noodles.

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%g}. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.
Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Fry until starting to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Stir in the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute}, then transfer the cooked veg to a medium #bowl{}. Set aside.

Pop the @cornflour{10%g} into a large bowl and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add the @diced British chicken thigh{190%g} to the bowl and toss to coat completely in the cornflour.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{} if needed.
Once hot, add the chicken. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, add the @egg noodle nests{2} and green beans to the pan of boiling water. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the cooked veg back into the pan.
Lower the heat to medium, then add the @ketjap manis{50%g}, @rice vinegar{30%ml}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce. Stir to combine and simmer until the sauce has reduced slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> See pantry for all three amounts of ketjap manis, rice vinegar, and tomato ketchup.

Remove from the heat, then taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

Add the cooked noodles and beans to the chicken stir-fry and toss to coat well in the sauce.
Share the sticky chicken noodles between your #bowls{}. Sprinkle over the spring onion to finish.

Enjoy!